==English==

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ædˈvaɪz.ɚ/

===Alternative spellings===
*[[Advisor]]

===Noun===
'''adviser'''  (''plural:'' '''[[advisers]]''')
# One who [[advises]].

====Usage note====
In the ''US'', an ''adviser'' has a connotation of someone offering unsolicited advice, while an ''advisor'' is someone speaking with a least some amount of wisdom or authority.

